title: NEIC, USGS,  24 hours since the Baja California 7.2 quake, North America, April 05, 2010
name: NEIC, USGS,  24 hours since the Baja California 7.2 quake, North America, April 05, 2010
description: The point shapefile shows the locations of 7.2 magnitude quake that struck near city of Mexicali in Baja California and 399 aftershocks in the last 24 hours since then. All are clustered around the southern edge of San Andreas fault.

author.source: National Earthquake Information Center, USGS website
